Prof Magoha also pointed out that between five to 10 teachers have been arrested for engaging in exam malpractices. 

He however cautioned students and teachers from being duped by fake KCSE papers in circulation in various Whatsapp groups.   Publisher, who had been contracted to supply books, reported that it could not trace four schools. Application window extended amid concerns that thousands of Form Four leavers were left out. President Kenyatta said the project seeks to enhance Kenyan’s self-reliance through local production of security equipment. The country had placed an order of 1.5 million doses in February this year. Sudan's government has declared a state of emergency in the region.